{"source_key":"sha256-4f3dcaa24e6b216c81e2c792e5295e32","record_index":274,"record_hash":"sha256:befdba1ca4195f2d05f860c5ee24d70f8699758e6a3aaa7bd562344a10cae4db","timestamp":"2026-05-24T14:42:05.985Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: cf1c7d\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1486\nOutput:\n   470\tThe UI should expose why a turn is highlighted. Reviewers should not have to\n   471\tguess why a session appears.\n   472\t\n   473\t## Privacy And Publication\n   474\t\n   475\tAgent Trail is more sensitive than local handoff because it is meant to be\n   476\topened by colleagues.\n   477\t\n   478\tBefore publishing or linking:\n   479\t\n   480\t- records must be redacted\n   481\t- local filesystem paths should not be exposed\n   482\t- raw provider session ids should not be exposed\n   483\t- hidden/system/developer prompts should not be exposed\n   484\t- source records should stay bounded and redacted\n   485\t- the user should understand that the trail may contain prompts and tool output\n   486\t\n   487\tThe first product design needs an explicit publication boundary. Capturing data\n   488\tinto GitMeta does not automatically mean every pull request should expose a\n   489\tpublic or team-visible Agent Trail.\n   490\t\n   491\t## Permissions\n   492\t\n   493\tFirst version: public repositories and public metadata only.\n   494\t\n   495\tThe server may generate or show an Agent Trail only when it can access the PR\n   496\tand GitMeta metadata without private credentials. Private repository support\n   497\tshould be a later design pass.\n   498\t\n   499\tFuture policy options:\n   500\t\n   501\t- GitButler team/workspace members\n   502\t- same users who can view the repository\n   503\t- same users who can view the pull request\n   504\t- explicit share link recipients\n   505\t\n   506\tFor private repositories, defaulting to repository/PR visibility is probably the\n   507\tleast surprising, but do not build that into v1.\n   508\t\n   509\t## Non-Goals\n   510\t\n   511\t- no claim that agent sessions authored the pull request\n   512\t- no full transcript dump as the main experience\n   513\t- no copying transcript records onto pull request targets\n   514\t- no product-specific review payloads inside `but-agentlog`\n   515\t- no magic generated summary as the \n[TRUNCATED]\nhted, and how the UI explains relevance without\n   550\t   claiming authorship.\n   551\t6. **Session browsing UX.** Lock the first-page structure: overview, sessions,\n   552\t   turn timeline, grouped records, validation, open questions, and raw evidence\n   553\t   drawer.\n   554\t7. **Failure states.** Define what the page shows for no access, no captured\n   555\t    data, weak relation evidence, redaction failures, too much data, and stale\n   556\t    GitMeta.\n   557\t8. **Retention and caching.** Decide whether generated trails are stored,\n   558\t    invalidated, expired, or rebuilt on demand.\n   559\t9. **Out-of-scope line.** Explicitly exclude compliance/audit guarantees,\n   560\t    full transcript publishing by default, automatic private publication, and\n   561\t    model-generated summaries as the source of truth.\n   562\t\n   563\tThe smallest buildable slice should prove the full path without solving every\n   564\tfuture policy:\n   565\t\n   566\t```text\n   567\tGitHub PR URL -> public access check -> metadata fetch -> but-agentlog lookup\n   568\t-> review-safe snapshot -> overview page -> session/turn drill-down\n   569\t```\n   570\t\n   571\tIf that path is vague, implementation should wait.\n   572\t\n   573\t## Remaining Answers Needed\n   574\t\n   575\tThe big shape is clear enough now: Forge-hosted, public-repo v1, on-demand URL\n   576\tentry, generated snapshots, server-side repo cache, GitMeta fetch, and\n   577\t`but-agentlog` interpretation.\n   578\t\n   579\tThere are no major architecture blockers left.\n   580\t\n   581\tResolved for v1:\n   582\t\n   583\t- canonical PR target key: PR number as a `but-agentlog` review target,\n   584\t  normalized to `gitbutler-review:<number>`\n   585\t- metadata ref path: fetch `refs/meta/main` from the public repository resolved\n   586\t  from the PR URL\n   587\t- lookup inputs: search the PR/review target and the PR head branch\n   588\t- ranking: review-target matches rank above branch-only matches\n   589\t- snapshot identity: PR number plus metadata ref OID plus selected session/turn\n   590\t  keys\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T14:42:05.985Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}